= How to configure a WildFly Bootable JAR as a systemd service

As a pre-requisite, you must have built a Bootable JAR.

== Create a wildfly user

    # groupadd -r wildfly
    # useradd -r -g wildfly -d /opt/wildfly-bootable -s /sbin/nologin wildfly

== Install a WildFly Bootable JAR

    # mkdir -p /opt/wildfly-bootable/bin
    # cp launch.sh /opt/wildfly-bootable/bin/
    # cp <your bootable JAR file> /opt/wildfly-bootable/wildfly-bootable.jar
    # chown -R wildfly:wildfly /opt/wildfly-bootable

== Configure systemd

    # mkdir -p /etc/wildfly-bootable
    # cp wildfly-bootable.conf /etc/wildfly-bootable/
    # cp wildfly-bootable.service /etc/systemd/system/
    
    # chmod +x /opt/wildfly-bootable/bin/launch.sh

== Start and enable

    # systemctl start wildfly-bootable.service
    # systemctl enable wildfly-bootable.service
